title: Delhi: Suicide bid at metro station, woman jumps before moving train | delhi | Hindustan Times
text:
Delhi: Suicide bid at metro station, woman jumps before moving train delhi Updated: Feb 20, 2017 13:21 IST New Delhi Metro services were disrupted for about ten minutes.(Sanjeev Verma/HT File Photo) 
A 25-year-old woman, working at a private hospital in Delhi, on Monday allegedly attempted to commit suicide by jumping before a Metro train. 
Officials said the incident was reported from the Guru Dronacharya station at about 7:30am when the woman identified as F Nishat allegedly jumped on the track even as the train bound for Samaypur Badli was moving in. 
The lady, an employee of a private hospital, suffered a fracture on her right hand and was immediately rushed to a nearby hospital. 
The police are trying to ascertain the reasons for her attempting the alleged suicide bid, they said. Read more
